    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I have been trying to add `# pragma: no cover` pragmas to [python-mbedtls](https://github.com/Synss/python-mbedtls/) but `coverage` with `Cython.Coverage` plugin still reports the lines.\r\n\r\nThe `no cover` pragma is [documented](https://coverage.readthedocs.io/en/coverage-5.1/excluding.html) in the coverage docs.\r\n\r\nSupport for excluding branches is possibly difficult but excluding lines would be a useful start.\r\n\r\nEDIT: I am working on a patch.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Here are some reasons why one would want this:\r\n\r\n* failed allocations (with `libc.stdlib.malloc`) handled with `raise MemoryError()` are hard to test, although this is the recommended way;\r\n* the `finally: free(buffer)` line following a malloc is also not marked as tested;\r\n* handling of older Python version with `if sys.version_info > (3, 6): import this; else: import that` cannot be covered in a single run with a single version of Python, yet coverage report of such code is largely irrelevant.\r\n",
            "created_at": "2020-06-12T08:37:48Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/3680#issuecomment-643150074",
